Haha, #iykyk! Had so much fun meeting Terry Lee Moore and his animals, especially Madonna, the boa constrictor! Terry is an animal specialist who has worked on movies as a stunt man and animal wrangler. If you watch an MGM film, that lion that roars, that was Terry's. Thank you @amangiri for setting up this private animal experience. We had so much fun. And thank you to Terry for being so kind and informative; Sadie especially loved meeting you and the animals. We will watch out for those scorpions and rattlesnakes while traveling.

I decided to conquer my fear of heights, and found that I really enjoy rock climbing. It was so freeing! I've always loved traveling, and experiencing new things. This time I am learning so much more about myself and what I can do!

This place is pure, natural beauty! Thank you so much to our guides at @uplakeadventures for bribing us to all these beautiful canyons along Lake Powell. If you are planning a trip to AZ/Utah, I highly recommend a ride on Lake Powell with Up Lake Adventures. #travel #amangiri

One of the highlights of my trip was walking down into this canyon. It was deserted and peaceful. Typically this landscape would be underwater, but because of global climate change, the water levels of Lake Powell have been drastically lower due to record low snowfalls in the mountainous areas surrounding it. While I was honored to walk through this canyon, Forbidden Canyon, that before the building of the Glen Canyon Dam was open like it was for me, it was a lesson in the realities of climate change and how human invention can change our natural landscapes. Before the dam, these canyons were a part of the Colorado River system. When the dam was built, in 1963, it flooded many of the canyons along the Colorado River and displaced many of the Navajo living along the river in canyons like this one; covering up historical sites in the process. I'm grateful to have walked along this canyon, where few have since 1963, but sad at how we are impacting this beautiful place. Thank you Bob and Mike from @uplakeadventures for your instruction on our trip. They are the kindest boat captains with an enormous wealth of knowledge about Lake Powell.
